main event: On June 9, 1959, a witness observed a very bright, white, oval-shaped object moving across the sky at an estimated altitude of 10,000 feet.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be between 2000-3000 yards away., The witness described experiencing a 'change' during the sighting., The object disappeared behind clouds after the observation., There were specific technical questionnaires filled out regarding the sighting., The report includes a section on the possible identification of the object as a balloon or aircraft.
witness description: Name redacted; personal details not provided
